Ad Text:
Drive insight.
Shape performance.
Influence decisions.
Amplitude Energy is seeking an experienced Senior Financial Analyst to play a critical role in strengthening financial insight, planning and performance capability. This senior, business-facing role is ideal for a commercially minded finance professional who thrives on partnering with leaders, elevating analysis quality, and enabling confident executive and Board decision-making.
  
About the Role
As the Senior Financial Analyst, you will lead Amplitude Energy’s financial planning cycles and deliver high-quality performance reporting that drives operational accountability and strategic value creation. You will coordinate the annual budget, quarterly forecasts and monthly leading estimates, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities.
  
Working closely with Operations, Projects and Corporate leaders, you will provide meaningful analysis, challenge assumptions, and influence commercial outcomes. You’ll also uplift reporting standards, develop models and dashboards, and champion continuous improvement within the FP&A function.
  
Key Responsibilities
Financial Planning & Analysis

Lead the end-to-end annual budget and forecasting processes, ensuring accuracy and alignment with business priorities.
Prepare Monthly Management Reports, leading estimates and executive-ready analysis.
Deliver high quality performance analysis and forward-looking insights, scenario modelling and performance commentary.
Translate operational data into meaningful insights that support strategic decisions.
Business Partnering

Act as a trusted advisor to Operations and Corporate leaders, providing financial guidance that drives accountability.
Lead cost-performance reviews, translate operational data into actionable insights and support commercial decision-making.
Represent Finance in cross-functional discussions to influence outcomes with evidence-based analysis.
Reporting & Continuous Improvement

Develop and refine financial models, dashboards and reporting templates for clarity and efficiency.
Support system and process improvements to streamline the FP&A cycle.
Ensure integrity, timeliness and accuracy across all financial submissions.
Leadership, Collaboration & Conduct

Take ownership from coordinating Finance’s planning calendar and key reporting deliverables.
Operate with autonomy, accuracy and professionalism, building confidence in financial outputs.
Support capability development within the finance team and uphold Amplitude Energy’s values.
Engage constructively with auditors, JV partners and key stakeholders. 
About You

CA / CPA qualified with a Degree in Accounting, Finance or Economics.
5–8+ years in FP&A, management reporting or business partnering, ideally in a complex or capital-intensive industry.
Proven leadership in budgeting and performance reporting for executive stakeholders.
Strong partnership experience with Operations or commercial teams.
Demonstrated ability to deliver insight-driven analysis that shapes decisions.
Advanced financial modelling capability.
Experience in ERP systems (SAP preferred) and reporting tools.
Attributes

Commercially astute, analytically rigorous and highly organised.
Strong communicator with the confidence to challenge and influence.
Proactive, resilient, collaborative and improvement-focused.
Why Join Us?
At Amplitude Energy, you’ll join a growing organisation where high-quality analysis is valued and where you can directly influence operational and strategic outcomes. You’ll work with a collaborative team committed to continuous improvement, professional excellence and supporting Australia’s energy future.
  
Like to know more?
If you’re interested in this opportunity, please apply using the link below. For a confidential discussion, contact Phil Scardigno at a&co Recruitment Partners on 0439 074 202 or email phil.scardigno@aandco.au

Job Title: Manager of AI, Innovation & Architectural Strategy
Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Our client, a leading organisation within the financial technology sector, is seeking an exceptional Manager of AI, Innovation & Architectural Strategy to shape the future direction of a flagship platform used widely across the Australian market.

This is a career-defining opportunity for a senior technology leader with deep experience across enterprise architecture, emerging technology, AI enablement and platform modernisation.

About the Technology Environment

You'll join a highly specialised technology division responsible for the full lifecycle management of one of Australia's most prominent platforms. The environment is diverse and multidisciplinary, spanning strategic planning, business and systems analysis, solution and enterprise architecture, software engineering, testing, and production support.

The team partners closely with business units across digital, client services, adviser experience, product, distribution, marketing, and finance-ensuring technology acts as a key enabler of commercial and customer success.

Role Impact

Reporting to the Head of Technology, the Manager of AI, Innovation & Architectural Strategy plays a pivotal role in defining the future state of the platform's technology landscape.

You will lead the adoption of cutting-edge AI capabilities, oversee architectural governance, and drive innovation to align with broader business and digital transformation strategies.

This role provides senior technical leadership, strategic oversight, and vendor engagement, representing the technology function in executive forums, industry events, and client-facing scenarios.

Primary areas of focus
Innovation, Architecture & AI Leadership

Own the portfolio of architecture, innovation and AI enablement, ensuring technology solutions are scalable, modern and future-proof.
Oversee architectural governance frameworks, cloud and platform modernisation, and AI-driven automation strategies.
Define new technology solutions in partnership with architects, analysts, and business leaders, ensuring alignment to enterprise standards and strategic objectives.
Drive AI and automation initiatives including machine learning, predictive analytics, and intelligent process automation.

Strategic Leadership & Governance

Establish best-practice technical disciplines and a centre of excellence for architecture, AI and innovation.
Provide senior advisory on architectural roadmaps, digital acceleration and innovation frameworks.
Act as a technical SME supporting the transition to contemporary architecture patterns and modern engineering practices.
Deliver executive-ready insights, presentations, and recommendations on technology strategy, risks and investment.

Vendor, Stakeholder & Executive Engagement

Manage strategic relationships with third-party vendors and technology partners to optimise the platform's innovation ecosystem.
Represent the technology function across executive forums, providing leadership on innovation and emerging technology capabilities.
Collaborate closely with program teams, PMO and transformation functions to ensure alignment between technology enablement and business priorities.
Maintain strong relationships across business units to support collaboration, advocacy and adoption of new technologies.

Experience Required

Extensive leadership experience in technology strategy, enterprise architecture, and AI-driven innovation.
Proven success consulting with senior business leaders to shape solutions aligned to organisational strategy.
Expertise across modern architectural frameworks including cloud-native technologies, microservices and API-led integration.
Deep understanding of AI and automation technologies-machine learning, NLP, intelligent automation.
Demonstrated experience delivering digital transformation and platform modernisation initiatives.
Strong vendor and partner management capability within complex enterprise technology environments.
Solid understanding of financial services, investment platforms, or similar complex technology ecosystems.

Qualifications

Tertiary qualifications in Information Technology, Computer Science, Engineering or Business.
Certifications in Enterprise Architecture (e.g., TOGAF), AI, cloud platforms or Agile delivery are highly regarded.

If this sounds like you please "Apply Now" or if you'd like a further discussion, feel free to contact Ronald Tran on O413 638 111 or ronald.tran@talentinternational.com.

Job Title: Senior Manager, Information and Data Governance
Category:
Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Hybrid work environment - 50% Office/Home
5-year Fixed Term Contract
Play an important part shaping the future of our iconic Australian institution


About the business/role/team


As Senior Manager, Information and Data Governance, you will report to the Deputy Head of Knowledge Management and lead a team of specialists across Information and Data Governance, Compliance and Architecture teams, where you will work closely with senior leaders in Risk, Technology, and Business Units to embed governance principles and enable data-driven decision-making.


This team sits within the Bank's Knowledge Management Department, which is central to enterprise information strategy and compliance.

About the role


Manage enterprise Information, Data, and AI governance frameworks, aligned with Commonwealth legislative requirements and Bank policy.
Manage the Bank's information classification framework, ensuring sensitive information is appropriately classified, handled, and protected, and maintain alignment with the Protective Security Policy Framework (PSPF), Australian Government Information Security Manual (ISM), and internal security standards.
Ensure compliance with recordkeeping obligations, including the Archives Act and relevant standards for digital and physical records.
Ensure that data models, standards, and platforms align with governance, security, and compliance requirements.
Partner with technology and business leaders to ensure governance supports innovation, analytics, and AI adoption while mitigating risk.
Champion cultural change by promoting information and data stewardship, security awareness, and information integrity across the organisation.


About you


Deep expertise in information and data governance, including regulatory compliance, risk management, and emerging AI governance practices.
Strong knowledge of Commonwealth information security and recordkeeping frameworks, including PSPF, ISM, and Archives Act requirements.
Proven leadership experience in complex organisations, ideally in financial services or government.
Strong stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence at all levels and drive enterprise-wide adoption of governance principles.
Familiarity with data platforms, metadata management, records management and governance technologies.


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.


Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Ad Text:

Position Title: Data Engineer and Reporting Specialist

Location: Preston

Why Join Us

Melbourne Polytechnic has been a leader in practical, real-world education since 1912. We offer:

Industry-led, hands-on training

About the Role

Melbourne Polytechnic is seeking a dynamic Data Engineer and Reporting Specialist to play a key role in the implementation of our new Student Management System (SMS). Reporting to the SMS Finance & Reporting Domain Lead, you will lead the development of a reporting strategy, automate operational and business intelligence reporting, and ensure data integrity across the student lifecycle.

This is an exciting opportunity to contribute to Melbourne Polytechnic’s Strategic Plan and Digital Strategy by delivering high-quality reporting solutions and dashboards that support informed decision-making.




Key Responsibilities

Develop and implement a comprehensive reporting strategy for the new SMS.

Design and support data integrations using Azure services (ADF, SQL Database, Data Lake, Synapse).

Lead reconciliation and gap analysis of reporting requirements across domains.

Design and build reports, dashboards, and templates using tools such as Power BI.

Build and optimise complex SQL queries and data warehouse models.

Collaborate with internal stakeholders and vendors to ensure timely delivery of reporting solutions.

Provide documentation, training, and post-go-live support for reporting tools.




Skills and Experience Required

Tertiary qualifications in IT, Business, or related field, or extensive experience in similar roles.

Strong experience in data engineering, ETL/ELT pipelines, and star-schema modelling.

Advanced SQL skills and experience with Azure services.

Proven ability to develop and publish Power BI dashboards and reports in an enterprise environment.

Exceptional stakeholder engagement and communication skills.

Ability to manage complex projects on time and on budget.




Additional Requirements

Successful candidate will be required to provide:

A valid Victorian Employee Working with Children Check (WWCC)

A National Police Check

Each file must be under 2MB. PDF is preferred (Word .doc or .docx also accepted). Avoid special characters in filenames (e.g., ! @ # % *).

Reference checks

Employment and qualification verification

Questions?

Contact: Recruitment Team

Email: recruitment@melbournepolytechnic.edu.au

Diversity and Inclusion

Melbourne Polytechnic is an equal opportunity and child-safe employer. We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people with a disability, people from diverse cultural backgrounds and gender identities.




Recruitment Agencies

Melbourne Polytechnic manages all recruitment directly. We do not accept unsolicited applications from agencies unless engaged through the State Purchasing Contract and with prior written approval.

Join the change. Electrify your future!

We've been proudly Aussie since 1837, always finding new ways to innovate in energy and essential services. Now, we're moving towards a sustainable future through electrification and investing in renewable energy-and we'd like you to join us. Whether you're on-site, in the office, or somewhere in between, you'll find opportunities to grow your career here. About the role

An exciting opportunity has become available for an Asset Data Quality Lead to join our Asset Services team based in Melbourne.
Reporting to the Manager, Asset Data and Governance, this is a unique opportunity to shape the future of Data and AI governance within our Energy Assets group. As our Data Quality Lead, you'll be the champion for turning industrial and enterprise data into our trusted assets. You'll design and deliver the frameworks, tools and processes that keep our data accurate, consistent and reliable.


Key responsibilities

Manage practical frameworks, tools and standards that improve the accuracy, consistency and
reliability of data.
Create clear data quality metrics and dashboards that give actionable insights.
Implement root cause fixes and sustainable solutions to data issues, preventing repeat problems.
Promote strong collaboration across business and technical teams to embed data quality and data management practices into everyday practice.
Translate strategic vision into actionable outcomes and embed data quality elements into
high-impact initiatives.
Become a trusted advisor, offering expert guidance on emerging risks, compliance requirements,
policies and guidelines that are integral to good data management practices.


About You

You're a collaborative data leader who helps teams embrace governance standards, and champions continuous improvement to deliver reliable, high-quality data and measurable business outcomes. Additionally, you will have most of the following:

Tertiary qualifications in Data Management, Computer Science, Information Systems, Statistics, Mathematics, or equivalent professional experience.
Demonstrated background and experience working in Data Management Practices,
particularly in Data Quality.
Advanced understanding of data quality's value, user adoption strategies, and
management.
Experience interpreting and analyzing data, using and managing data quality tools,
dashboards, and validation processes.
Prior experience with various technology products and services such as Azure products,
cloud storage, SQL servers, SAP, Power BI.
Good working knowledge of the energy market and the convergence of Operational Technology and Information Technology.


Applications close on 7 December 2025

2-3 days on site in Clayton with flexibility to work from home.





About Us: 

DuluxGroup is a leading marketer and manufacturer of premium brands that help people create better spaces to live and work. With a heritage of over 100 years, we’re home to trusted names like Dulux, Selleys, Yates, Cabot’s, and B&D, delivering products across paints, coatings, adhesives, garden care, and home improvement. As part of Nippon Paint Holdings, we combine global scale with strong local roots, driven by innovation, sustainability, and a commitment to our customers. 

Our Group Functions cover Supply Chain, Sales Capability, Finance, People & Culture, IT & Digital, and Legal are an integral part of our Business Units that enable growth and operational excellence. They provide the insights, technology, and expertise that keep our businesses agile and future ready. Joining DuluxGroup means contributing to iconic brands, working in a collaborative culture, and enjoying opportunities for career growth and flexibility. 

What You’ll Be Doing: 

Lead finance for DuluxGroup’s Distribution & Freight network, overseeing a $110M cost base across five state warehouses and national freight operations. As the key financial partner to the Head of Distribution, you’ll manage budgeting, forecasting, month-end reporting, and strategic analysis while contributing to leadership decisions.

This hybrid role blends financial oversight with operational projects, including freight optimization, S&OP, and inventory planning. You’ll work closely with numerous stakeholders across finance and operations, mentor a direct report, and drive process improvements to enhance efficiency and cost control. 

Our Benefits: 

Up to $1,000 net annually to cover private health extras gap costs 
Exclusive discounts on DuluxGroup products and partner offers 
Stay active anytime, anywhere through our partnership with Fitness Passport 
20 weeks paid parental leave (primary carers) and 2 weeks partner leave from day one 
Market leading learning, development and career pathways 
Access to our Wellbeing Hub and full EAP support 
Recognition programs that celebrate your impact 

What We’re Looking for: 

Degree in Accounting or related discipline, with CA/CPA qualification (or currently studying).
Relevant industry experience ideally in supply chain, distribution, freight, manufacturing, FMCG, or retail.
Strong financial management background, including budgeting, forecasting, and P&L oversight.
Advanced financial modelling and evaluation skills, with solid commercial acumen.
Proficiency in key systems such as SAP and strong analytical capability.
Excellent communication and influencing skills, able to engage across diverse stakeholders. 

Why Join Us? 

Progressing your career with the DuluxGroup means being part of a network of over 8000 employees globally who believe in our purpose to ‘Imagine a Better Place’ 

With origins dating back to 1918, we are a leading marketer and manufacturer of iconic brands such as Dulux, Selleys, Cabots, Yates and B&D to name a few.  

By joining us, you will be a part of a long-term strategy to deliver profitable growth through brand leadership, innovation and customer intimacy. We are committed to internal mobility and growth while fostering an inclusive culture with flexible work options. 

If this sounds like an environment you would like to be a part of, please apply online!

Company description:



Deloitte Services Pty Ltd



Job description:


Career development - receive support and coaching to further your Workday consulting career
Flexible work arrangements - work in a way which suits you best
Work on high-profile client projects with a world class team

Are you an experienced, passionate pioneer in technology - a solutions builder, a roll-up-your-sleeves technologist who wants a daily collaborative environment, think-tank feel and share new ideas with your colleagues?

What will your typical day look like?

Based in Sydney or Melbourne, as a Workday Integration Manager within Deloitte's HRT practice, you should expect to be client facing and involved in the following:

Client Work

Define, build and test Workday integrations
Using your HCM and/or Financials experience to determine effective integration solutions
Work with 3rd party vendors on integration solutions
Dependent on seniority, responsible for:
Oversight of integration delivery
Manage integration approach for design and build
Point person for integration in partnership with the Integration Director
Directs team to design and build integrations

Practice Development

Offering a strong and compelling point of view around integration approaches and design
Contributing to continuous improvement of the delivery and innovation of integrations
Actively involved in the running of the practic

Business Development

Playing an active role in pre-sales and bid development
Identification of on-sell opportunities through existing client engagements
Actively contribute to the growth of the business by delivering sales opportunities

About the team
Sitting within Human Capital Consulting, our forward-thinking team specialises in all things tech. We revamp the way our client companies work and craft beautifully-designed, fully integrated systems with solutions like SAP, Oracle, and Workday.

Enough about us, let's talk about you
Our practice is growing, and we're keen to speak with individuals at all levels who have experience in integrating cloud-based ERP systems

Qualifications

Required:

Experience with at least 2-3 full life cycle cloud system implementation or the support and enhancement of a Workday system post go-live.

Preferred:

Workday Integration Certified, strongly preferred but not required
Consulting experience, preferably with a large consulting firm
Superior Communication Skills, both written and oral

Even if you don't have Workday experience, but are well versed with another technology, like PeopleSoft, SAP or Oracle and want to make the switch…we still want to hear from you.

Why Deloitte?

At Deloitte, we focus our energy on interesting and impactful work. We're always learning, innovating, and setting the standard; making a positive difference to our clients and our society. We put coaching at the heart of what we do, helping our people grow their careers in any direction - whether it be up, moving into something new, or even moving across the world.

We embrace diversity, equity, and inclusion. We have a diverse collection of people from different backgrounds, with different experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. What binds us together is a shared commitment to value everyone's perspective and to cultivate inclusion; so that our work environment is a safe space we can all belong.

We prioritise flexibility and choice. At Deloitte, you get trust on Day 1. We know our people get their best work done when they're in control of where and how they work, designing their work week around their client, team, and personal commitments.

We help you live and work well. To support your personal and professional life, we offer a range of perks and benefits, including retail discounts, wellbeing leave, paid volunteering days, twelve flexible working options, market-leading parental leave and return to work support package.

Next Steps

If you have questions regarding this role the Talent Acquisition Team is available to have a confidential discussion. Regarding this role, you can contact Abhi Bassi via the Our Recruiters section on our career's website.

Position Overview

We are seeking a strategic and technically skilled Senior Project Manager to lead advanced HR data analytics, workforce planning, and cross-functional coordination across enterprise platforms. This role will support executive decision-making through robust reporting, data governance, and stakeholder engagement, while ensuring seamless operational transition and compliance.


Key Responsibilities
Lead development of HR dashboards and reports using tools such as Power BI, Calumo, and Snowflake.
Manage data integrations across platforms including Workday, Ascender, and Adaptive Planning.
Ensure data governance, quality assurance, and role-based security models are in place.
Drive workforce planning and position management aligned with financial forecasting.
Support cost variance analysis and executive-level reporting (e.g., EG and EG-1 dashboards).
Collaborate with Finance to optimise use of Adaptive Planning for budget cycles.
Coordinate deliverables across multiple program streams including Staff Analytics, HR Establishment, and Academic Workload Planning.
Manage interdependencies and ensure alignment with strategic objectives.
Facilitate engagement with HR, Finance, IT, BIR, and Health stakeholders.
Lead working groups, steering committees, and reference groups.
Track benefits, ensure audit compliance, and report to regulatory bodies (e.g., TEFMA, UniForum, TASCI).




Qualifications & Experience
Proven experience in HR data analytics and workforce planning in large, complex environments.
Higher Education industry experience
Strong technical proficiency in Power BI, Snowflake, Adaptive Planning, and enterprise HR systems.
Demonstrated ability to lead cross-functional teams and manage executive-level reporting.
Experience in change management, governance, and compliance frameworks.
Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement, and project coordination skills.

The role

We have an exciting opportunity in our People & Development (P&D) team, focussing on people analytics, reporting and reward on a full-time basis. In this role, you will report to the Performance & Reward Manager and be responsible for developing and managing people related data and insights for both internal and external reporting. Contributing to Clayton Utz's reward strategies, you will provide analysis and advice that supports the design and delivery of our innovative reward solutions. You will be using Workday and collaborating closely with our Systems and the Business Intelligence (BI) team.


Key responsibilities 

Coordinate the annual and interim fixed and variable remuneration review processes.

Lead the budgeting and cost analysis; and remuneration reporting tasks associated with the annual review.

Build reporting solutions and insights to support the P&D team and the business with their people data needs.

Provide analytical and research support to the design and delivery of innovative reward strategies.

Work collaboratively with the Talent & Performance Consultant, and the Systems team.

Provide benchmarking and interpretation of external remuneration data, as well as market data submissions and validations.

Produce and maintain any regular and ad-hoc reporting required (weekly/monthly/annually) for external bodies and key stakeholders.




Skills & Experience


To be successful in this role, you will have: 

A proven analytical/statistical background.

3 years plus reward experience, preferably in the professional services or legal industry.

Previous systems experience, preferably with Workday.

Minimum 2 years of HR/Data management and reporting experience.

Excellent Excel skills for building complex data and reporting models.

Exposure to Business Intelligence tools such as Power BI is favourable.

Strong skills in gathering business requirements and managing stakeholders.

Strong attention to detail.

Resilience and the ability to work autonomously.

 In addition, we are looking for a motivated self-starter who has an interest in working in a fast paced and dynamic environment. 

The National People & Development team

With a presence in all our major offices, the National People and Development (P&D) team advises the business on all people initiatives, including talent management, employee relations, resourcing, recruitment (both graduate and lateral), remuneration, benefits, reporting and learning and organisational development.

Our client is a leading energy provider with a strong focus on meeting regulatory obligations while delivering reliable outcomes for customers. Their teams support major reforms across the sector, driving change across people, process and technology to keep the business compliant and future ready.

You will play a key role in overseeing how the organisation responds to industry reforms and regulatory change. Your focus is end to end traceability, clear assessment of business impacts and strong alignment with legal, compliance and risk teams. You will scope incoming regulatory work, guide delivery teams through EPIC and story assurance, and support change adoption across the business. This role suits someone who enjoys structure, clarity and ownership across complex regulatory programs.

About You

Strong experience as a Senior Business Analyst within the energy sector
Background in regulatory or compliance driven projects
Skilled in impact assessments, risk alignment and detailed requirements analysis

Opportunity to shape the organization’s data and AI strategy

Data quality, ingestion rate, and availability

Company Description

Working with our clients across real estate, infrastructure, energy and natural resources, we transform together delivering outcomes that improve people’s lives. Job Description


We are seeking an exceptional Associate Director to drive growth in the market, lead strategic client relationships, and help us achieve our ambitious growth targets over the coming years. Due to increasing demand for our Infrastructure Digital – Data and Analytics services, this role will play a critical part in expanding our capabilities and delivering data excellence across our team and client engagements. We are looking for a commercially and technically minded leader with a proven track record of delivering successful data-driven solutions. The ideal candidate will be skilled in managing relationships and providing technical guidance across a multidisciplinary team spanning data visualisation, automation, infrastructure, data science, and systems implementation.

The Role

As the Associate Director, your responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:

Leverage a strong technical background to effectively engage with both clients and technical teams.
Lead client engagements, define delivery strategies, and provide technical assurance across complex data and analytics projects.
Manage and deliver system deployments across critical PMO functions, including cost control, schedule management, and risk mitigation.
Design, develop, and implement data-driven solutions in collaboration with clients and internal teams to generate actionable insights and enhance performance.

Ad Text:
Senior Analyst - Simulation Delivery

Permanent full-time role within the ISP - Value Chain Performance (VCP)

Perth based role - Central Park

A work environment where safety is always the number one priority

We encourage women and Indigenous Peoples to apply, as we advance our business to more accurately reflect the world around us.


Where we're all welcome 

We are committed to an inclusive environment where people feel comfortable to be themselves. We want our people to feel that all voices are heard, all cultures respected and that a variety of perspectives are not only welcome - they are essential to our success. We treat each other fairly and with dignity regardless of race, gender, nationality, ethnic origin, religion, age, sexual orientation or anything else that makes us who we are. 

At Rio Tinto, we particularly welcome and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, women, the LGBTI+ community, mature workers, people with disabilities and people from different cultural backgrounds. 

We acknowledge that all people are different and believe that our differences are our strength.  The diversity of skills, life experiences and perspectives within our team enhances our way of working and our ability to achieve success together.    

About the role

We are seeking a Senior Analyst - Simulation Delivery to join our ISP - Value Chain Performance (VCP) division.

This role offers an exciting opportunity to make a tangible impact on how we plan and operate across the entire Rio Tinto Iron Ore (RTIO) supply chain.

As part of our Simulation Modelling team, you will play a critical role in delivering data-driven insights that support strategic decision-making. This position provides exposure to discrete event simulation tools and the chance to develop a holistic understanding of our end-to-end supply chain - from pit to port.

You will work closely with diverse teams across RTIO, collaborating with stakeholders at all levels to drive optimisation and influence key business outcomes.

Reporting to the Principal Simulation Delivery, you'll be at the heart of turning complex data into actionable insights that shape strategic decisions.

Your work will span across analytics, simulation, and stakeholder engagement, giving you a unique opportunity to influence how our supply chain operates. Key aspects of the role include:

Data Analytics & Insights - Collect, process, and analyse large operational datasets to create model inputs, validate results, and uncover insights that drive decision-making.

Simulation Experimentation - Design and run simulation experiments to answer critical business questions using scenario analysis and sensitivity testing.

Model Validation & Assurance - Ensure models accurately reflect real-world performance through rigorous validation and calibration.

Problem Framing - Define and structure analytical problems, selecting the right approach to deliver robust solutions.

Supply Chain Systems Understanding - Analyse interactions across mines, rail, and port systems to identify bottlenecks and optimisation opportunities.

Communication & Storytelling - Translate complex findings into clear, compelling narratives and visualisations that enable confident decisions.

Stakeholder Engagement - Build strong relationships with stakeholders, ensuring alignment, transparency, and successful delivery.

What you'll bring

A commitment to the safety of yourself and your team

Positive attitude with a willingness to make a difference

We're looking for a motivated and curious professional who enjoys solving complex problems and working collaboratively. Ideally, you'll have experience in the following areas:

Data Analysis - Strong analytical skills with proficiency in Python (highly desirable) or other analytical tools.

Problem Framing - Ability to define problems clearly and structure analytical approaches effectively.

Simulation Analysis - Experience setting up simulation experiments and interpreting results (preferred but not essential).

Supply Chain Knowledge - Understanding of the integrated mining supply chain, including how mines, rail, and port operations interact.

Communication - Skilled at translating complex analyses into clear, actionable insights for decision-making.

Stakeholder Engagement - Ability to build collaborative relationships and manage delivery outcomes effectively.

A C Class Manual drivers' licence

Note: Prior simulation modelling experience is advantageous but not mandatory.

If you are excited about the role and think you have what it takes but your experience doesn't align 100% we still want to hear from you. 

What we offer

Be recognised for your contribution, your thinking and your hard work, and go home knowing you've helped the world progress.

A work environment where safety is always the number one priority

A permanent position working directly for Rio Tinto

A competitive base salary reflective of your skills and experience with annual incentive program

Comprehensive medical benefits including subsidised private health insurance for employees and immediate family

Attractive share ownership plan

Company provided insurance cover

Extensive salary sacrifice & salary packaging options

Career development & education assistance to further your technical or leadership ambitions

Ongoing access to family-friendly health and medical wellbeing support

Leave for all of life's reasons (vacation/annual, paid parental, personal & cultural leave)

Exclusive employee discounts (banking, accommodation, cars, retail and more)

Possible domestic relocation assistance

We are committed to elevating Indigenous voices and increasing cultural knowledge in our business. Diversity of skills, life experiences and perspectives within our team enhances our way of working and our ability to achieve success together. To help you on your journey with us, you'll also have access to:

Specialist Indigenous Support Advisors are always there for our Indigenous employees and available to support through any aspect of your employment

Where you'll be working

You and your team will be Perth-based with opportunity to work flexibly from home combined with time in our Central Park offices. There will be the opportunity for some Pilbara site travel from time to time, however this will be performed on an ad-hoc basis.

In the Pilbara region of Western Australia, we own a world-class, integrated network of 17 mines, four independent port terminals, a rail network spanning nearly 2,000 kilometres and related infrastructure - all designed to respond rapidly to changes in demand. We are one of the world's leading producers and exporters of iron ore.

Our privately owned and operated rail network is an essential part of our integrated production process and services our 16 mines across the Pilbara via almost 2,000 km of track. With rail depots located at Tom Price, Cape Lambert and Dampier (7 Mile), most trains are autonomously operated and typically comprise three locomotives and 240 ore cars stretching to approximately 2.4 kilometres in length. We are also applying and adapting technology to improve safety and productivity across our rail network.

Who we are

Rio Tinto is a leading global mining and materials company. We operate in 35 countries where we produce iron ore, copper, aluminium, critical minerals and other materials needed for the global energy transition and for people, communities, and nations to thrive.

We have been mining for 150 years and operate with knowledge built up across generations and continents. Our purpose is finding better ways to provide the materials the world needs - striving for innovation and continuous improvement to produce materials with low emissions and to the right environmental, social and governance standards. But we can't do it on our own, so we're focused on creating partnerships to solve problems, create win-win and meet opportunities.

Job Title: Director Consulting Expert – Data And AI
Ad Text:
Position Description:


SUMMARY: 
Your future role and responsibilities:

. Lead enterprise-scale data and AI transformation programs, encompassing strategy, architecture, governance, and delivery.
. Advise C-suite and senior executives on leveraging data and AI to drive operational excellence, innovation, and new business models.
. Exceptional skills in Proposal development, SoW development and tender/bid responses.
. Develop and implement enterprise data strategies including data mesh, data fabric, governance, MDM, and ethical AI frameworks.
. Shape and deliver AI and ML initiatives, such as predictive analytics, generative AI adoption, automation, and intelligent decision support.
. Support business development by identifying opportunities to expand CGI's Data and AI footprint across industries.
. Create and present thought leadership—whitepapers, frameworks, and client briefings—on emerging trends such as generative AI, responsible AI, and data democratisation.
. Mentor and coach CGI consultants, developing future leaders in data science, analytics, and AI engineering.
. Collaborate across CGI's global network to align local delivery with global best practices in Data and AI innovation.
. Foster a culture of experimentation, curiosity, and continuous learning, promoting data literacy across the business.

Experience required to be successful in this role:

. Recognised as a leader in the field by alliance partners, including but not limited to AWS, Azure, Databricks, Snowflake and GCP.
. Proven experience leading enterprise data and AI transformation programs (e.g., data platform modernisation, AI/ML initiatives, analytics strategy).
. Strong understanding of data architecture, data engineering, governance, and cloud-based analytics platforms (AWS, Azure, Databricks, Snowflake and GCP).
. Expertise in AI technologies and frameworks (e.g., machine learning, NLP, computer vision, GenAI platforms).
. Demonstrated success advising senior executives and influencing strategic decision-making through data insights.
. Excellent business development and client relationship management skills, with a track record of growth in consulting engagements.
. Exceptional leadership, communication, and stakeholder management abilities.
. Relevant certifications in Data, AI, or Cloud.
. Experience with data ethics, AI governance, and regulatory compliance is advantageous, especially in regulated industries such as Financial Services.

What you can expect from us:


Together, as owners, let’s turn meaningful insights into action.

Life at CGI is rooted in ownership, teamwork, respect and belonging. Here, you’ll reach your full potential because…

You are invited to be an owner from day 1 as we work together to bring our Dream to life. That’s why we call ourselves CGI Partners rather than employees. We benefit from our collective success and actively shape our company’s strategy and direction.

Your work creates value. You’ll develop innovative solutions and build relationships with teammates and clients while accessing global capabilities to scale your ideas, embrace new opportunities, and benefit from expansive industry and technology expertise.

You’ll shape your career by joining a company built to grow and last. You’ll be supported by leaders who care about your health and well-being and provide you with opportunities to deepen your skills and broaden your horizons.

Come join our team—one of the largest IT and business consulting services firms in the world.
